The Peace Tower was built to commemorate the birth of this figure, but the 
U.S. forced its partial removal due to the presence of the Imperial slogan "Eight World 
Regions Under One Roof." One theory claims this figure was actually an alchemist 
named Xu Fu [[SHOO FOO]], who served (+) Qin Shi Huang Di and travelled eastward 
during one region's Yayoi period. The three-legged crow Yata-Garasu led this 
mythical figure to the land of Yamato, where his forces defeated the Emishi people to 
dominate the island of (*) Honshu. The first mythical emperor of Japan was, for the points, 
which direct descendant of Amaterasu?=====
Emperor Jimmu =====